{Content 
    styleTitle="h2"
    title="Cyberbullying Remains One of Major Suicide Factors Among Teenagers"
    blockBg='dark'}
    <div id="grid-images" class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-9 col-md-9 col-sm-9">
            <div class="pt15 pb20">
                <ul>
                    <li>As reported by CNN, Hope Sitwell was 13 years old, when she hanged herself after her ex-boyfriend shared a picture of her breasts among students of six different schools in Florida.</li> 
                    <li>13 year-old Megan Meier struggled with attention deficit disorder and had issues with her weight. She hanged herself after one of her best Facebook friends said he didn’t want to be friends anymore and messaged “The world would be a better place without you.”</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Most children take the online reality too seriously. They consider it is their true life, have many friends, communicate, and spend most time on the web. Parents should also consider this and keep kids safe online the same way they do in the offline world. Nothing but constant parental control can prevent our loved once from incautious actions.</p>
            </div>
        </div>    
        <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 col-sm-3 text-center">
            <img alt="stop cyberbullying with Pumpic" src="{$img}/geo-lending/img_1.png" width="207px" height="208px" />
        </div>
    </div>
{EndContent}

{Content 
    styleTitle="h2"
    title="The Government Takes Action"
    blockBg='light'}
    <div id="grid-images" class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 col-sm-3 text-center">
            <img alt="how usa government fights cyberbullying" src="{$img}/geo-lending/geo-lending_usa.png" width="207px" height="208px" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-9 col-md-9 col-sm-9">
            <div class="pt30 pb20">
    
                <p>Online safety in the USA is crucial and the government is deeply involved in the issue. The Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) and the Children’s Internet Protection Act (CIPA) stand on guard of child Internet safety regulating main principles and restrictions of online access for the underage.</p>
                <p>Thus, there allowed to be no 18+ content advertised on kid related web sources as well as data collection restrictions are specified, when it comes to children. However, as practice shows, the government cannot provide Internet safety for children of each family in the U.S. That's why protecting kids online is the top priority of parents.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
{EndContent}

